        June’s album reviews coming up below!

        I got through more than I expected, so I’ll just choose five of them that were either popular in the mainstream or surpassed my personal expectations.
        The albums I’ll be covering are;

        - ‘I Used To Think I Could Fly’ by Tate McRae
        - ‘Mellow Moon’ by Alfie Templeman
        - ‘Twelve Carat Toothache’ by Post Malone
        - ‘Gold Rush Kid’ by George Ezra
        - ‘Bridges’ by Calum Scott

        Also reviewed Alice Merton, Chase & Status, Sigma & The Chainsmokers this month if anybody’s curious to see those! 👀
